OL,4,Corder is 'meaningless sentence'
OL,6,FWhen asked if she and the rest of the
OL,7,Ffamily were given any choice in the
OL,8,Fmatter of the lesser plea of
OL,9,Fmanslaughter, she replied: "No choice
OL,10,Fwhatsoever, it was just sprung on us -
OL,11,Fjust like this family.
OL,13,F"There was no choice. It was just done
OL,14,Fand dusted by the CPS."
OL,16,FYemi has been fighting for change with
OL,17,Fthe help of her MP since her sister
OL,18,Fwas killed 16 years ago.
