OL,6,FOn the question of offenders being
OL,7,Fable to plead guilty to manslaughter
OL,8,Fon the grounds of diminished
OL,9,Fresponsibility, the Ministry of
OL,10,FJustice (MOJ) has reiterated that no
OL,11,Fpatient can be released without the
OL,12,Fexpress approval of the Secretary of
OL,13,FState and those releases can be
OL,14,Fblocked if they are deemed to be a
OL,15,Fdanger to the public.
OL,17,FOn the second point, the MOJ said it
OL,18,Fwas in a judge's power to impose one
OL,19,Fof those Section 45A orders - but in
OL,20,FAbi's case and the Nottingham case,
OL,21,Fthe judge opted against doing so.
